Project 1 Analysis

Import libaries and data

library("readxl")
data = read_excel("data.xlsx")

Testing that “Hard Punch” is reliable 70% of the time. Null hypothesis is that hard_punch_success <= 70%

t.test(data$hard_punch_success, alternative = "greater", mu = 7)

    One Sample t-test

data:  data$hard_punch_success
t = 2.56, df = 12, p-value = 0.0125
alternative hypothesis: true mean is greater than 7
95 percent confidence interval:
 7.350519      Inf
sample estimates:
mean of x 
 8.153846

Testing that “Precision Spin” is reliable 70% of the time. Null hypothesis is that spin_success <= 70%

t.test(data$spin_success, alternative = "greater", mu = 7)

    One Sample t-test

data:  data$spin_success
t = 15.398, df = 12, p-value = 1.44e-09
alternative hypothesis: true mean is greater than 7
95 percent confidence interval:
 9.380677      Inf
sample estimates:
mean of x 
 9.692308

Testing that we don’t have false activations of “Hard Punch” when performing “Precision Spin”. Testing that we don’t have false activations of “Precision Spin” when performing “Hard Punch”.

Two sample T-test

t.test(x=data$punch_activation_when_expect_spin, y= data$spin_activation_when_expect_punch, paired=TRUE)

    Paired t-test

data:  data$punch_activation_when_expect_spin and data$spin_activation_when_expect_punch
t = -0.89776, df = 12, p-value = 0.387
alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
95 percent confidence interval:
 -0.7908341  0.3292957
sample estimates:
mean of the differences 
             -0.2307692

Testing that we don’t have false activations when walking.

Two-sample T-test

t.test(x=data$punch_activations_during_walk, y= data$spin_activations_during_walk, paired=TRUE)

    Paired t-test

data:  data$punch_activations_during_walk and data$spin_activations_during_walk
t = 0.61721, df = 12, p-value = 0.5486
alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
95 percent confidence interval:
 -0.3892431  0.6969354
sample estimates:
mean of the differences 
              0.1538462

Testing that we don’t have false activations when drawing. Two sample T-test

t.test(x=data$punch_activations_during_draw, y= data$spin_activations_during_draw, paired=TRUE)

Boxplot section

boxplot(data$hard_punch_success, main="Hard Punch Reliability",
   xlab = "Hard Punch", ylab="Number successes per 10")

boxplot(data$spin_success, main="Precision Spin Reliability",
   xlab = "Precision Spin", ylab="Number successes per 10")

boxplot(data$spin_activation_when_expect_punch, main="Joint Punch Reliability",
   xlab = "Accidental Precision Spins", ylab="Amount per 10")

boxplot(data$punch_activation_when_expect_spin, main="Joint Spin Reliability",
   xlab = "Accidental Hard Punches", ylab="Amount per 10")

boxplot(data$activations_during_walk, main="Accidental Activation during Everyday Activities",
   xlab = "Accidental Activations", ylab="Number per trial")

boxplot(data$activations_during_draw, main="Accidental Activation during Phone Use",
   xlab = "Accidental Activations", ylab="Number per trial")
